You could try to add the [css-vars-ponyfill](https://www.npmjs.com/package/css-vars-ponyfill) polyfill to use it in IE browser, code sample as below:

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://unpkg.com/css-vars-ponyfill@2/dist/css-vars-ponyfill.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/js-beautify@1/js/lib/beautify-css.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt; 
    &lt;script&gt;
        cssVars({ 
            // Treat all browsers as legacy
            onlyLegacy: false, 
        });

    &lt;/script&gt;
    &lt;style &gt;
        :root {
            --bg-color: green;
        }
        .main {
            display: inline-block;
            background: var(--bg-color);
            width: 200px;
            height: 200px;
